1.Configure your compilation environment

Download and install msys2,and then install the required compiler in msys2：

pacman -S gcc make cmake svn base-devel mingw-w64-i686-toolchain
 

2.Install the tinc dependency library

pacman -S libreadline ncurses zlib liblzo2 
pacman -S libreadline-devel ncurses-devel zlib-devel liblzo2-devel 


3.Compilation of libmyfec

git clone https://github.com/dnetlab/libmyfec.git
cd libmyfec
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -G "MSYS Makefiles"
make   
make install DESTDIR=/usr/myfec     (Be sure to eliminate Spaces in directory names，mv or cp -a)


4.Compilation steps of tinc

git clone https://github.com/dnetlab/tinc.git

autoreconf -fsi

./configure  --build=i686-w64-mingw32 --host=i686-w64-mingw32 --with-curses-include=/usr/include/ncurses --with-myfec-include=/usr/myfec/libmyfec/myfec/include --with-myfec-lib=/usr/myfec/libmyfec/lib

 (the Path is the path your files installed.)

make  (generate tincd.exe tinc.exe)



